Transport Minister Dipuo Peters will visit the Hope Restoration Ministries in Kempton Park during road safety campaign on Sunday.The visit is as part of her stakeholder engagement to intensify road safety education and awareness.State owned transport agencies with a mandate on road safety and roads will accompany the Minister during her road safety exhibition at Hope Restoration Ministries.Minister Peters will be joined by the Minister of Basic Education Angie Motshekga during her visit.Last week, Minister Peters released the festive season road death statistics for 2016.A total of 1,714 fatalities were recorded in this festive period, which is a 5% increase on the previous period.The minister stated that her department had already recorded more than 800 fatalities on the country s roads since the beginning of the festive season.-TNA Reporter 